title: Idaho Wolf Project
creator: David Ausband
description: The Idaho Wolf Project has 3 study areas near Salmon, Lowman, and Kellogg, Idaho. The project wants to explore the effects of hunting and trapping on gray wolves in Idaho. So far, hunting and trapping has reduced pup survival by 50%. The Idaho Wolf Project has been genetically sampling wolves in Idaho since 2007, with future plans to assess whether hunting and trapping are affecting wolf behaviors (i.e., propensity to disperse).
subject: University of Idaho; wolves; biology

title: Flori Tulli's Graduate Project Proposal
creator: Flori Tulli
description: This recording is the project proposal for my English M.A. non-thesis about wolf reintroduction in Idaho. Rather than write a 30-40 page theoretical paper, I want to create a multimodal project that encapsulates visual art and an interactable webpage. My goal is to create a project that brings together the different viewpoints surrounding wolf presence, demonstrating how they create a complex landscape.

title: Jaws of Life
creator: Flori Tulli
description: This sculpture/fountain was a product of my previous investigation into trophic cascade, a drastic ecosystem change caused by the absence of predators. Working on this project showed me the possibilities of art and ecology in portraying complex ecological relationships, such as the interconnectivity of wolves to deer, beavers, and water tables.
